\section*{Introduction; what is it and why?}
PianoScript is a music notation for pianists that like to read music in a visual and practical way. It aimes to be a tool and can be extended as full replacement but that is certainly not the goal of the project. The main goal is to provide a tool that plots the rhythm and harmony of a midifile in a readable design.\\

PianoScript is based/inspired by an almost hundred year old music notation called 'Klavarskribo'. There are a small number of eye-catching visual differences that make PianoScript a different music notation. Besides that PianoScript is only aiming for piano music/players in its current design so the user can learn and practice the music from this printed plot.\\

The main reason PianoScript was born is that Philip Bergwerf discovered Klavarskribo and begun searching for improvements and different possibillities in terms of visual design as well practical readabillity of the notation itself.\\


The document has two parts:
\begin{itemize}
\item Tutorial of the PianoScript music notation; We explain the music notation in detail.
\item Manual for PianoScript software; To be able to use the notation there is a piece of software called PianoScript. In this part we explain the software in detail.
\end{itemize}

You can use the four-bar example of the Moonlight Sonata by Beethoven to refer to while reading the document.

